    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>.cs file modification in BFF (SearchResult model + projection in SemanticSearchEndpoints). ADR-008/010/029 binding. BFF additions governance applies (Placement Justification required per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Per FR-BFF-01, extend the `SearchResult` shape and the `/api/ai/search` projection to include `modifiedAt: DateTime?` (ISO datetime) and `modifiedBy: string?` (display name). Source: standard system fields `modifiedon` and `modifiedby` on `sprk_document`. Existing fields and behavior unchanged. Existing clients unaffected. Add an integration test that asserts the projection includes both new fields. This task is consumed by task 041 (Documents PCF list-view default sort `modifiedAt DESC`).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 / Minimal API developer with deep familiarity with the BFF (`Sprk.Bff.Api`), the Semantic Search endpoint pipeline (`SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs`, `SearchResult.cs`, the Dataverse post-search lookup step), and BFF additions governance (`.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SearchResult.cs` gains `ModifiedAt: DateTimeOffset?` ([JsonPropertyName("modifiedAt")]) and `ModifiedBy: string?` ([JsonPropertyName("modifiedBy")]) properties following the existing `CreatedAt` / `CreatedBy` shape. `SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs` (and any post-search Dataverse projection helper) populates both fields from `modifiedon` and `modifiedby` system fields on `sprk_document`. Existing field projections + behavior unchanged. Existing clients unaffected (additive shape only). Integration test asserts the projection returns both new fields. Builds clean. ADR-008 endpoint filter unchanged. ADR-010 DI minimalism preserved (no new services). ADR-029 publish hygiene preserved (no new NuGet, no publish-size delta beyond noise).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec.md §Owner Clarifications: "Project BOTH `created*` AND `modified*`; default sort `modifiedAt DESC`". This is the canonical Owner-Clarified decision behind FR-BFF-01. The Documents PCF list view (task 041) needs `modifiedAt` for default sort and `modifiedBy` (with avatar + name) for the Modified by column.

      `SearchResult.cs` already has `CreatedAt` / `CreatedBy` shaped exactly the way we need — this task adds the mirror pair for the modify lifecycle. The Dataverse post-search lookup step (which already populates `CreatedBy` from a Dataverse fetch) is the obvious place to also fetch `modifiedon` / `modifiedby`.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/SemanticSearch/SearchResult.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/SemanticSearch/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-BFF-01 — add modifiedAt + modifiedBy to SearchResult and projection; source modifiedon + modifiedby on sprk_document</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-BFF-01 — existing fields and behavior unchanged; existing clients unaffected (additive only)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint filter pattern preserved (SemanticSearchAuthorizationFilter unchanged)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — no new service registrations; reuse existing Dataverse lookup service</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — no new NuGet packages; no transitive CVE introductions; publish-size delta within noise (NFR-06)</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">BINDING — Placement Justification required in PR description even though answer is "in BFF (additive projection)"</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-008-endpoint-filters.md</file>
