  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Step 0.5: This task does NOT touch Fluent v9 React components — `fluent-v9-component` skill is NOT applicable. Skip.</step>
    <step order="1">Load knowledge: `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` (binding pre-merge checklist), ADR-008/010/029, `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md`.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `SearchResult.cs` to confirm the `CreatedAt`/`CreatedBy` property shape; mirror it for `ModifiedAt`/`ModifiedBy`. Use `DateTimeOffset?` (matching `CreatedAt`) and `string?` (matching `CreatedBy`). XML doc comments mirror the Created* docs.</step>
    <step order="3">Add the two properties to `SearchResult.cs` with `[JsonPropertyName("modifiedAt")]` and `[JsonPropertyName("modifiedBy")]`.</step>
    <step order="4">Locate the Dataverse post-search lookup in the Semantic Search pipeline (likely in `Services/Ai/SemanticSearch/`). It already fetches `createdby` for the `CreatedBy` field. Extend that fetch + projection to also populate `ModifiedAt` (from `modifiedon`) and `ModifiedBy` (from `modifiedby` lookup display name) on each `SearchResult`.</step>
    <step order="5">Verify no new DI registrations are needed (ADR-010). If the change introduces any new service, push back — extension should be in the existing lookup service.</step>
    <step order="6">Add an integration test (in the existing Sprk.Bff.Api test project — find via Glob for `*Test*.cs` near SemanticSearch) using `WebApplicationFactory` that POSTs to `/api/ai/search`, gets back a `SemanticSearchResponse`, and asserts: (a) at least one result has non-null `ModifiedAt`; (b) at least one result has non-null `ModifiedBy`; (c) all existing fields (`DocumentId`, `Name`, `CreatedAt`, `CreatedBy`, etc.) are still present.</step>
    <step order="7">Build verification: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` clean; run the new integration test; `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` shows no new HIGH CVE.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify publish-size impact: `dotnet publish src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ --runtime linux-x64 -c Release` and confirm output size delta &lt; 100 KB (additive property changes are noise-level; flag if delta is unexpectedly large).</step>
    <step order="9">Document the Placement Justification in the PR description per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` §A.1: "Additive projection on existing /api/ai/search endpoint. Latency-sensitive (consumed in user-facing list view), reads BFF-managed Dataverse post-search lookup in same request — belongs in BFF. No new services, no new packages, no publish-size impact."</step>
    <step order="10">Step 9.5 (FULL rigor): run `Skill code-review` + `Skill adr-check` — fix issues before completing.</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 050 → ✅. Update current-task.md to next pending task.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
