    <criterion testable="true">code-review + adr-check pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The existing SearchResult already has CreatedAt (DateTimeOffset?) + CreatedBy (string?) — mirror that exactly. The Dataverse post-search lookup (which already populates CreatedBy from a Dataverse fetch) is the natural place to add modifiedon + modifiedby. No endpoint filter changes; no new services; no new packages. This is a textbook "additive projection" change — but per BFF governance, the Placement Justification is still required in the PR.

    The integration test should use the existing test fixture pattern (find via Glob for `*WebApplicationFactory*` or similar in the test project). If no existing Semantic Search integration test exists yet, this task adds the first one.
  </notes>

